Document: BackBufferCopy
Path: godot/classes/class_backbuffercopy.rst
Summary: The CopyMode enumeration defines three buffering modes for the BackBufferCopy node.

CopyMode enumeration:
COPY_MODE_DISABLED = 0: Disables the buffering mode. This means the BackBufferCopy node will directly use the portion of screen it covers.
COPY_MODE_RECT = 1: Buffers a rectangular region.
COPY_MODE_VIEWPORT = 2: Buffers the entire screen.
---CHUNK---
Document: BackBufferCopy
Path: godot/classes/class_backbuffercopy.rst
Summary: Properties for configuring the BackBufferCopy's mode and area.

copy_mode (CopyMode): Determines the buffer copy behavior. Default: 1. Note: Buffer mode. Set via set_copy_mode(CopyMode), retrieved via get_copy_mode().

rect (Rect2): Defines the area covered by the BackBufferCopy. Default: Rect2(-100, -100, 200, 200). Note: Only used if copy_mode is COPY_MODE_RECT. Set via set_rect(Rect2), retrieved via get_rect().